moderate_difficulty: One or more medical problems (ASA Class 2*)

high_difficulty: Extreme gag reflex which has compromised past dental care
Confusing and complex signs and symptoms: difficult diagnosis
minimal_difficulty: Signs and symptoms consistent with recognized pulpal and periapical conditions
moderate_difficulty: Extensive differential diagnosis of usual signs and symptoms required

high_difficulty: Extreme difficulty obtaining/interpreting radiographs (e.g., superimposed anatomical structures)
moderate_difficulty: Moderate difficulty obtaining/interpreting radiographs (e.g., high floor of mouth, narrow or low palatal vault, presence of tori)

high_difficulty: Extensive pretreatment modification required for rubber dam isolation
moderate_difficulty: Simple pretreatment modification required for rubber dam isolation

high_difficulty: Restoration does not reflect original anatomy/alignment
Significant deviation from normal tooth/root form (e.g., fusion, dens in dente)
moderate_difficulty: Moderate deviation from normal tooth/root form (e.g., taurodontism, microdens)

high_difficulty: Mandibular premolar or anterior with 2 roots
Canal divides in the middle or apical third
moderate_difficulty: Crown axis differs moderately from root axis. Apical opening 1-1.5 mm in diameter

minimal_difficulty: Canal(s) visible and not reduced in size
moderate_difficulty: Canal(s) and chamber visible but reduced in size

high_difficulty: Complicated crown fracture of immature teeth
minimal_difficulty: Uncomplicated crown fracture of mature or immature teeth
moderate_difficulty: Complicated crown fracture of mature teeth

high_difficulty: Previous access with complications (e.g., perforation, non-negotiated canal, ledge, separated instrument)
Previous surgical or nonsurgical endodontic treatment completed
Root amputation prior to endodontic treatment
